From: Wayen Yan <win847@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] thermal: airoha: Fix low trip clamp variable

The low-trip branch clamps high into low. Clamp the requested low threshold so
low and high thermal events remain independent.

Signed-off-by: Wayen Yan <win847@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
+++ b/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
@@ -373,7 +373,7 @@ static int airoha_thermal_set_trips(stru
 
 	if (low != -INT_MAX) {
 		/* Validate low and clamp it to a supported value */
-		low = clamp_t(int, high, RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, 0),
+		low = clamp_t(int, low, RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, 0),
 			      RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, FIELD_MAX(EN7581_DOUT_TADC_MASK)));
 
 		/* We offset the low temp of 1°C to trigger correct event */
